  "response_text": "The total energy of foragers in the Megafaunal Hunting Pressure Model (MHPM) shows a consistent downward trend over the simulation period. Initially, the total energy of foragers starts around 0 and remains relatively stable for a short period. Around the 500-step mark, the total energy begins to decline steadily. By approximately 1000 steps, the total energy of foragers has decreased to around -10,000 units. This downward trend continues linearly, reaching about -20,000 units by 1500 steps. The decline persists, and by the end of the simulation at 2000 steps, the total energy of foragers drops to approximately -35,000 units. Throughout the simulation, the rate of energy decline remains consistent, indicating a steady decrease in the energy status of the foragers over time."
}

